      <hedline>
        <hl1>Rocker on the Subway</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Christina McCarthy letter says John Rocker of Atlanta Braves should travel subway to Shea Stadium as New Yorkers do, without police escort</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Rocker's Subway Ride Creates Security Headaches'' (Sports pages, June 22):</p>
        <p>If John Rocker, the Atlanta Braves relief pitcher, wants to take the No. 7 train to Shea Stadium next week, then he should do so on his own, as many New Yorkers do daily.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Rocker's Subway Ride Creates Security Headaches'' (Sports pages, June 22):</p>
        <p>If John Rocker, the Atlanta Braves relief pitcher, wants to take the No. 7 train to Shea Stadium next week, then he should do so on his own, as many New Yorkers do daily.</p>
        <p>Why should New York City deploy extra police and plainclothes officers for Rocker? Of course these officers can be put to better use.  Most New Yorkers tend to ignore celebrity sightings anyway. If John Rocker is not ignored, then he will have brought this attention upon himself, and he should have to deal with the consequences alone.</p>
        <p>CHRISTINA MCCARTHY  New York, June 22, 2000</p>
      </block>
